nodes.documentation:
This is a contract manages the various SW asset factories
and ensures that each factory has constraint access in
terms of the id space they are allowed to mint.
@dev Mint permissions use range because factory contracts
     could be minting large numbers of NFTs or be built
     with granular, but efficient permission checks.

devdoc.details: Mint permissions use range because factory contracts     could be minting large numbers of NFTs or be built     with granular, but efficient permission checks.

params._factory: Address of the factory to activate
Address of the factory to update permission
params._maxRange: Maximum ID (inclusive) in id range that factory will be able to mint
params._minRange: Minimum ID (inclusive) in id range that factory will be able to mint

params._owner: The address of the token holder

batchBurn(uint256[],uint256[]).details: This will not change the current supplies tracked in _supplyManagerAddr.

batchMint(address,uint256[],uint256[],by.details: This methods assumes ids are sorted by how the ranges are sorted in     the corresponding mintAccessRanges[msg.sender] array. Call might throw     if they are not.

params._amounts: Array of amount of tokens to mint per id
params._data: Byte array of data to pass to recipient if it's a contract
params._to: The address to mint tokens to.

lockRangeMintPermissions((uint256,uint25.details: THIS ACTION IS IRREVERSIBLE, USE WITH CAUTIONIn order to forever restrict minting of certain ids to a set of factories,     one first needs to call `addMintPermission()` for the corresponding factory     and the corresponding ids, then call this method to prevent further mint     permissions to be granted. One can also remove mint permissions after ids     mint permissions where locked down.

params._range: AssetRange struct for range of asset that can't be granted              new mint permission to

params._tokenIDs: Array of IDs of tokens to log default URI

params._data: Data to pass if receiver is contract
params._to: The address to mint tokens to

params._factory: Address of the factory to update permission
params._rangeIndex: Array's index where the range to delete is located for _factory

safeBatchTransferFrom(address,address,ui.details: MUST emit TransferBatch event on success Caller must be approved to manage the _from account's tokens (see isApprovedForAll) MUST throw if `_to` is the zero address MUST throw if length of `_ids` is not the same as length of `_amounts` MUST throw if any of the balance of sender for token `_ids` is lower than the respective `_amounts` sent MUST throw on any other error When transfer is complete, this function MUST check if `_to` is a smart contract (code size > 0). If so, it MUST call `onERC1155BatchReceived` on `_to` and revert if the return amount is not `bytes4(keccak256("onERC1155BatchReceived(address,address,uint256[],uint256[],bytes)"))` Transfers and events MUST occur in the array order they were submitted (_ids[0] before _ids[1], etc)

params._data: Additional data with no specified format, sent in call to `_to`

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: MUST emit TransferSingle event on success Caller must be approved to manage the _from account's tokens (see isApprovedForAll) MUST throw if `_to` is the zero address MUST throw if balance of sender for token `_id` is lower than the `_amount` sent MUST throw on any other error When transfer is complete, this function MUST check if `_to` is a smart contract (code size > 0). If so, it MUST call `onERC1155Received` on `_to` and revert if the return amount is not `bytes4(keccak256("onERC1155Received(address,address,uint256,uint256,bytes)"))`

params._data: Additional data with no specified format, sent in call to `_to`

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: MUST emit the ApprovalForAll event on success

params._approved: True if the operator is approved, false to revoke approval
params._operator: Address to add to the set of authorized operators

setBaseMetadataURI(string).details: Will update the base URL of token's URI

params._newBaseMetadataURI: New base URL of token's URI

setMaxSupplies(uint256[],uint256[]).details: Can only decrease the max supply if already set, but can't set it *back* to 0.

params._ids: Array of token IDs to set the max supply
params._newMaxSupplies: Array of max supplies for each corresponding ID

params._factory: Address of the factory to shutdown

uri(uint256).details: URIs are defined in RFC 3986.     URIs are assumed to be deterministically generated based on token ID     Token IDs are assumed to be represented in their hex format in URIs

userdoc.notice: This is a contract manages the various SW asset factories and ensures that each factory has constraint access in terms of the id space they are allowed to mint.
